==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spirometer
<hw>Spi*rom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>spirare</ets> to breathe + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <def>An
instrument for measuring the vital capacity of the lungs, or the volume
of air which can be expelled from the chest after the deepest possible
inspiration. Cf. <er>Pneumatometer</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spirometry</ent>⟦br⟧
